Study Title: Oral Topotecan Versus Intravenous Docetaxel In Pretreated, Advanced Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer
Brief Summary: The purpose of this study is to collect information on how effective and how well tolerated an oral investigational drug is compared to a standard intravenous drug in patients with pretreated, advanced non-small lung cancer (NSCLC).
Secondary Outcome Measures: overall survival, time to progression, response rate, response duration, time to response, improvement in quality of life and patient well-being, and qualitative and quantitative toxicities.
Study Design: Allocation: RANDOMIZED|Intervention Model: PARALLEL|Masking: NONE|Primary Purpose: TREATMENT
